{"id":2271,"category_slug":"medical-english-oet","category_name":"Medical English (OET)","position":6,"title":"Test 01 - Part B - Extract 4","subtitle":"Bed Management Challenges","level":"B2","parts":14,"url":"https://dailydictation.com/exercises/medical-english-oet/test-01-part-b-extract-4.2271/listen-and-type","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/medical-english-oet/test-01-part-b-extract-4-2025-08-29-21-03-23/0-test-01-part-b-extract-4.mp3","transcript":"The bed manager just rang.\nHe wants us to clear three spaces in the ward today.\nOh, it's never-ending!\nLet's see what we can do.\nThere's no one ready to be discharged.\nBut we could try chasing referrals for Mr Davison to the community hospital for rehab.\nWhere are his notes?\nYes, but has he had his assessment yet?\nThey were all away at that conference yesterday and the day before.\nI think he'll have slipped through the net.\nBut Doctor Ammat's already got him medically stable and signed off, so...\nhe should be the next one to move on.\nWell I'd get him there as quickly as possible before they give the place to somebody else.\nI'll phone them straight away.","youtube_video_id":"","details_cached_at":"2026-06-15T20:52:37","challenges":[{"position":1,"content":"The bed manager just rang.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/medical-english-oet/test-01-part-b-extract-4-2025-08-29-21-03-23/1.mp3","time_start":0.49,"time_end":2.03},{"position":2,"content":"He wants us to clear three spaces in the ward today.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/medical-english-oet/test-01-part-b-extract-4-2025-08-29-21-03-23/2.mp3","time_start":2.03,"time_end":5.09},{"position":3,"content":"Oh, it's never-ending!","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/medical-english-oet/test-01-part-b-extract-4-2025-08-29-21-03-23/3.mp3","time_start":5.09,"time_end":7.49},{"position":4,"content":"Let's see what we can do.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/medical-english-oet/test-01-part-b-extract-4-2025-08-29-21-03-23/4.mp3","time_start":7.49,"time_end":9.47},{"position":5,"content":"There's no one ready to be discharged.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/medical-english-oet/test-01-part-b-extract-4-2025-08-29-21-03-23/5.mp3","time_start":9.86,"time_end":12.21},{"position":6,"content":"But we could try chasing referrals for Mr Davison to the community hospital for rehab.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/medical-english-oet/test-01-part-b-extract-4-2025-08-29-21-03-23/6.mp3","time_start":12.21,"time_end":17.16},{"position":7,"content":"Where are his notes?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/medical-english-oet/test-01-part-b-extract-4-2025-08-29-21-03-23/7.mp3","time_start":17.47,"time_end":18.59},{"position":8,"content":"Yes, but has he had his assessment yet?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/medical-english-oet/test-01-part-b-extract-4-2025-08-29-21-03-23/8.mp3","time_start":18.51,"time_end":20.55},{"position":9,"content":"They were all away at that conference yesterday and the day before.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/medical-english-oet/test-01-part-b-extract-4-2025-08-29-21-03-23/9.mp3","time_start":20.55,"time_end":24.01},{"position":10,"content":"I think he'll have slipped through the net.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/medical-english-oet/test-01-part-b-extract-4-2025-08-29-21-03-23/10.mp3","time_start":24.12,"time_end":26.38},{"position":11,"content":"But Doctor Ammat's already got him medically stable and signed off, so...","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/medical-english-oet/test-01-part-b-extract-4-2025-08-29-21-03-23/11.mp3","time_start":26.38,"time_end":30.41},{"position":12,"content":"he should be the next one to move on.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/medical-english-oet/test-01-part-b-extract-4-2025-08-29-21-03-23/12.mp3","time_start":30.41,"time_end":32.07},{"position":13,"content":"Well I'd get him there as quickly as possible before they give the place to somebody else.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/medical-english-oet/test-01-part-b-extract-4-2025-08-29-21-03-23/13.mp3","time_start":32.07,"time_end":36.41},{"position":14,"content":"I'll phone them straight away.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/medical-english-oet/test-01-part-b-extract-4-2025-08-29-21-03-23/14.mp3","time_start":36.41,"time_end":37.75}]}